7bd20e58-0b97-5a4e-a5ad-6063398493d2,tg:rubgr:1187,e73_Descriptions,,id.desc,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,"[vouwblad] [recto] Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Return of Herd; An Autumn picture: In Stchavinskiy Collection [Sobranie kartin V.A. Shchavinskago = Collection W. Stchawinsky], Petrograd ,1917], 'N° 77, C.[Cornelis] Massys' (Witt Library under C. Matsys) which certainly is not by C. Massys, but early XVII, with a diagonal river landscape on the right & developed from Bruegel, appear several Autumn motifs (August-Sept.-Oct. or Sept.-Oct.-Nov.?[sic] On left [onleesbaar] picking apples, left foreground people with grapes in baskets. In central middle ground: sower. In right foreground turned towards right bottom corner: Herd of cattle being driving home by man on white horse, dressed exactly like in Bruegel with; [verso] hat of the same type, brim in front turned up and with a Heeveless 'Kapuze'. He holds a long pole in his gloved right hand. In front of him a man on foot with a long steel driving the cattle, at his side a smaller one (a young boy?[sic], walking with his long stick [onleesbaar].The picture is not copied from Bruegel, but probably inspired by him. The garnements of the cattle drivers in a Flemish picture show that not alpine dress (against Haberlandt!)[= Arthur Haberlandt, 'Das 'Herbstbild' oder 'Die Heimkehr der Herde' Peter Bruegels d.Ä., in: Karl Ilg (Hrsg.), Beiträge zur Volkskunde Tirols. Festschrift für H. Wopfner, 2. Teil, (Schlern-Schriften; 53), Innsbruck: Wagner, 1947-1948]",descriptive note,Nederlands,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

column4: <content>[vouwblad] [recto] Ad [Addendum] Bruegel: Return of Herd; An Autumn picture: In Stchavinskiy Collection [Sobranie kartin V.A. Shchavinskago = Collection W. Stchawinsky], Petrograd ,1917], 'N° 77, C.[Cornelis] Massys' (Witt Library under C. Matsys) which certainly is not by C. Massys, but early XVII, with a diagonal river landscape on the right & developed from Bruegel, appear several Autumn motifs (August-Sept.-Oct. or Sept.-Oct.-Nov.?[sic] On left [onleesbaar] picking apples, left foreground people with grapes in baskets. In central middle ground: sower. In right foreground turned towards right bottom corner: Herd of cattle being driving home by man on white horse, dressed exactly like in Bruegel with; [verso] hat of the same type, brim in front turned up and with a Heeveless 'Kapuze'. He holds a long pole in his gloved right hand. In front of him a man on foot with a long steel driving the cattle, at his side a smaller one (a young boy?[sic], walking with his long stick [onleesbaar].The picture is not copied from Bruegel, but probably inspired by him. The garnements of the cattle drivers in a Flemish picture show that not alpine dress (against Haberlandt!)[= Arthur Haberlandt, 'Das 'Herbstbild' oder 'Die Heimkehr der Herde' Peter Bruegels d.Ä., in: Karl Ilg (Hrsg.), Beiträge zur Volkskunde Tirols. Festschrift für H. Wopfner, 2. Teil, (Schlern-Schriften; 53), Innsbruck: Wagner, 1947-1948]</content>

<part_of.title>Ad [Addendum] 24. Ad Bruegel: Return of Herd. C. [Cornelis] Massys, Witt Library; A painting called Cornelis Massys probably a picture of Autumn clearly connected with Bruegel's Return of Herd; in Stchawinsky, Coll. Petrograd [= Shchavinskiy collection Sobranie kartin V.A. Shchavinskago = Collection W. Stchawinsky. Petrograd 1917] , N° 77; Left: Fruitbasket, Centre: Sowing, Right: Return of Herd; A picture of the Summer P. de Boer, A[mster]dam 1938: 10. a Cornelis Metsys, Paysage avec une auberge, bois 23 x 27, seems to be part of the same series.</part_of.title>
<object.title>The Months: The Return of the Herd</object.title>
